# Force LF line endings across all platforms.
#
# WHY: the repo builds + ships binaries on Linux/macOS/Windows CI runners.
# Windows git defaults to `core.autocrlf=true` and converts LF → CRLF on
# checkout for text files, which breaks:
#   - //go:embed scripts (embedded bytes differ → idempotent installs drift)
#   - golden-file tests (generated Go output is LF, golden would be CRLF)
#   - any test that hashes/compares file contents verbatim
#
# This attribute ensures every checkout sees the same bytes the blob holds.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly mark binary assets so normalization leaves them untouched.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.db binary
*.tar binary
*.gz binary
*.zip binary

# Shell scripts and golden fixtures are explicitly LF — they're either
# executed by /bin/sh on POSIX or compared byte-for-byte by Go tests.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.golden text eol=lf
